  "time_ut": 1657050195,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Agricultural loan waiver",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The economic crisis in the country has been exacerbated by the Easter Sunday attack and the subsequent Covid-19 pandemic, which has had both direct and indirect impacts on all sectors in general.",
        "This situation is difficult for the farmers who are 30 percent of the total population to bear, and the decision to introduce the use of natural fertilizers instead of the use of chemical fertilizers has caused the farmers to face many more difficulties.",
        "Under this situation, it has become impossible to repay the loan amount received by the farmers for rice cultivation and the banks have classified the said loans as non-dischargeable loans.",
        "Therefore, as more farmers are likely to be unable to obtain the required credit for the upcoming bumper rice crop, it is essential to provide incentives to them through government intervention.",
        "Accordingly, the Cabinet has given its approval to waive off the initial loan amount of loans taken from the State Bank for paddy cultivation on land of two hectares or less and which are now unable to be repaid.",
        "The Cabinet has approved the proposal submitted by Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe as Minister of Finance, Economic Stability and National Policy."
      ],
